# Reports Are Not Ontologies

| Layer | What it contains | Defined by |
|---|---|---|
| **TBox** (schema) | Entity types, relationships, vocabulary | `domain.yaml` + `application/core/models/` |
| **ABox** (assertions) | Specific entities and their property values | Reports, ingestion pipeline |
| **Reasoning** | Patterns, significance, recommendations | The LLM agent, at query time |

Reports populate the ABox. The domain schema provides the TBox. The agent is the reasoner.

## Authority rules

- `REPORT_CAN_CREATE` in `application/ingestion/rules.py` — which entity types each report type may create
- `REPORT_FIELD_AUTHORITY` in `application/ingestion/rules.py` — which fields each report type owns (overwrites vs fills gaps)
- `_PROPERTY_AUTHORITATIVE_TYPES` in `application/ingestion/operations.py` — which report types may create new Properties

A delinquency report cannot create properties. A rent roll is authoritative for `occupancy_status`. A lease expiration report only enriches empty fields.

## Do not recreate

The **entailment engine** (precomputed signal evaluators) was deleted — it encoded business judgment as code. The agent discovers patterns from data.
